        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How are you?' (to a male)"
        },
        "text": "When asking a male 'How are you?', you can use 'Kif dayer?' or the more general 'Lbas?' which means 'Are you well?'. 'Lbas?' is widely used for both genders.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كِيفْ دَايَرْ؟",
            "english": "How are you? (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Kif dayer?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "لَبَاسْ؟",
            "english": "Are you well? / How are you? (to male or female)",
            "transliteration": "Lbas?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
